analyses.message:
Refactor REST API system to use IRequest and JsonProperty; Allow http requests for now

Replaces the custom FieldAttribute with Newtonsoft.Json's JsonProperty for DTO field mapping, introduces the IRequest interface for request DTOs, and updates Function and RestApiService to use reflection for parameter and body serialization. Updates all relevant request/response code, removes FieldAttribute, and updates documentation to reflect the new attribute and interface system. Also adds net.gree.unity-webview to manifest, and enables Android project export.

WIP Add authentication OTP endpoint; wip restapi field attribute

Introduced new classes for the authentication OTP (OptRequest, OptDto, OptResponse) and related test scripts. Added FieldAttribute for request field mapping. Updated RestApiService with new request overloads and refactored IFunction. Cleared default API configs in RestApiServiceConfig.

commit_details.message:
Refactor game history to use MockGame model

Replaced usage of MockMatch[] with a new MockGame struct throughout game history and details UI. Updated prefabs and scripts to support additional game metadata (date, type, total score, etc.), and added UI elements for completion status (green check/red X) and date/type display. This improves data structure consistency and enhances the game history presentation.

Add back and create profile buttons to GameModeScreen

Introduces serialized fields and UI bindings for back and create profile buttons in GameModeScreenView and updates the prefab accordingly. Also improves localization fallback in GameDetailsPopupView and GameHistoryWidget, and fixes score formatting in GameDetailsPopupView.

Refactor GameDetailsScreen to popup and update widgets

Renamed GameDetailsScreen to GameDetailsPopup, updating related prefabs, scripts, and references. Refactored GameDetailsScreenView to GameDetailsPopupView, removed mock data from the popup, and added support for opening the popup from GameHistoryWidget. Updated GameHistoryWidget to use match data, display correct scores, and open the details popup. Added mock data utilities to GameModeScreenView and improved CustomContentSizeFitter with a delayed update method.

Refactor GameDetailsScreenView and update UI prefabs

Refactored GameDetailsScreenView to inherit from GenericPopupContent and merged SetSwingsData and SetStatisticsData into a single SetMatchesData method. Updated related prefab anchors and size settings to match the new logic. Adjusted mock data handling and improved prefab assignment checks for better error handling.

Refactor GameDetailsScreen UI and add widgets

Updated GameDetailsScreen and related prefabs to improve layout and naming, reducing unused children and adjusting size parameters. Introduced new StatisticsItemWidget and SwingStrokeWidget scripts and their meta files. Updated GameDetailsScreenView to reference new UI elements and prefabs, and refactored CustomContentSizeFitter. These changes support a more modular and maintainable UI structure for game mode details.

Add Game Details screen and related UI assets

Introduced new UI prefabs and scripts for the Game Details screen, including GameDetailsScreen, GameDetailsStatisticsItem, SwingItem, SwingStrokeItem, and Switch. Added corresponding widgets and view scripts. Updated UI configuration and added/renamed several UI art assets to support the new screen.

Add yellow icon and update GameHistoryWidget logic

Added a yellow icon asset and integrated it into the GameHistoryItem prefab. Updated GameHistoryWidget to show the green icon when all holes are played and the yellow icon otherwise, with new SetHolesPlayedAndTotal logic. Also refactored CustomContentSizeFitter to improve RectTransform handling and made various UI adjustments in GameModeScreen.

Add paginated loading to match history screen

Introduced a 'Load More' button to the GameModeScreen, enabling paginated loading of match history. Refactored GameModeScreenView to support incremental data loading, item clearing, and improved UI state management for loading and error scenarios.

commit_details.message:
Call DelayedUpdateSize instead of UpdateSize

Replaces the call to _contentSizeFitter.UpdateSize() with DelayedUpdateSize() in GameModeScreenView. This may address timing issues with UI layout updates after changing the page index.

Refactor UI widgets and views for improved data handling

Refactored GameDetailsView and SwingItemWidget to improve mock data handling and item clearing logic. Added ScrollRect support and content size updates for better UI responsiveness. Updated AvatarWidget initialization and GameModeScreenView to clear items and update size on load more. These changes enhance maintainability and ensure UI elements are properly refreshed when data changes.

Add animated GameDetailsView and dark background

Introduces an animated open/close behavior for GameDetailsView using a coroutine and adds a dark background overlay. Updates GameHistoryWidget to reference the view directly, and adjusts GameModeScreenView to ensure the load more button is always last in the hierarchy. Prefab and asset changes support these UI improvements.

Add AvatarWidget UI component and integration

Introduces the AvatarWidget prefab, associated script, and supporting assets for displaying user avatars in the GameMode screen. Updates GameModeScreen.prefab to use the new widget and removes the previous TMP text implementation, improving modularity and maintainability of the avatar display logic.

Clarify TODO comments for mock data methods

Updated TODO comments in several UI classes to specify that mock data methods should be removed when actual game data is implemented and tested. This improves clarity for future code maintenance.

Integrate real match and map data into game UI

Replaced mock data methods with new methods that accept real GolfMatchModel, MapData, and GolfShotModel objects across GameDetailsView, GameModeScreenView, GameReplayView, GameHistoryWidget, SwingItemWidget, StatisticsItemWidget, and SwingStrokeWidget. Updated UI prefabs and widgets to display actual match, map, and shot data, and added logic to handle data loading and presentation. This refactor prepares the UI for integration with live match history and map configuration services.

Refactor GameReplayView UI update logic

Consolidated repeated UI update code into a single UpdateUI method in GameReplayView.cs, improving maintainability and reducing duplication. Removed redundant event from StatsPanel.prefab.

Add navigation for holes and strokes in GameReplayView

Introduces next/previous hole and stroke navigation buttons to GameReplayView, updates button states, and refactors data passing to include game and match context. Also updates SwingItemWidget and SwingStrokeWidget to support new navigation and context requirements, and improves mock video URL selection in GameModeScreenView.

Add GameReplayView and related UI components

Introduces GameReplayView, ReplayStatWidget, and VideoNavButton prefabs along with their scripts and meta files. Refactors GameDetailsPopup to GameDetailsView and updates related scripts to support new replay and video navigation features in the GameMode UI.

commit_details.message:
Add TrainingLab popups and widgets, refactor GameMode

Introduces new TrainingLab UI popups and widgets, including TrainMenuPopUp and IconButtonWidget. Refactors GameMode-related prefabs and scripts by moving GameDetailsView and related files to TrainingLab/GameMode, and updates references and naming for consistency. Also updates several UI prefabs and scripts to support the new TrainingLab features.

Add achievement status icons and child selector

Introduced UiChildSelector for managing child visibility and animated transitions. AchievementWidget prefab now supports 'in progress', 'done', and 'canceled' status icons, and AchievementWidget.cs is updated to handle an add button. UI layout adjustments were made to CoachFeedbackView and MyTrainingLabLandingScreen prefabs for improved alignment and sizing.

Add ReviewSummary widget and update TrainingLab UI

Introduced ReviewSummaryWidget and its prefab for the TrainingLab UI. Updated MyTrainingLabLandingScreen to remove legacy status and date elements, refactored text and layout, and removed the coaching history button. Adjusted CoachFeedbackView and VideoWidget prefabs to support new UI structure.

Refactor TrainingLab UI prefabs and scripts

Moved CoachFeedbackView prefab and meta from MainMenu to TrainingLab folder, added CoachingHistoryScreen and related scripts, and reorganized widget prefabs under TrainingLab. Updated MyTrainingLabLandingScreen and several scripts to support new UI structure and features.

Adjust UI anchors and refactor StageProgressWidget

Updated anchor and position values for several UI elements in MyTrainingLabLandingScreen.prefab to improve layout. Refactored StageProgressWidget.cs by making _stageIndex a private field instead of a serialized field.

Add round rect shader and stage progress UI components

Introduces a new RoundRectShader (Shader Graph, material, and controller script) for UI elements. Adds StageProgressWidget and related scripts for stage progress display. Updates TrainingPlanWidget and relevant UI prefabs to integrate new shader and progress components. Also adds ColorExtensions utility.

Add FeedbackSent prefab and update GiveFeedbackView

Introduced a new FeedbackSent prefab for the dark theme UI. Updated GiveFeedbackView.prefab and its layout to support the new feedback sent state, including changes to button arrangement and UI structure. Modified GiveFeedbackView.cs to support the updated UI flow.

Add GiveFeedbackView UI and related widgets

Introduced the GiveFeedbackView prefab and associated widget prefabs for the TrainingLab UI, including BottomText, RequestButton, and StandardButton. Updated TrainMenuPopUp and MyTrainingLabLandingScreen prefabs to integrate the new feedback functionality. Moved ColorExtensions.cs to Scripts.Core/Extensions. Added GiveFeedbackView script and made minor adjustments to CoachFeedbackView and related UI scripts to support the new feedback flow.

Refactor TrainingLab UI and add CoachWidget

Removed inline CoachWidget from MyTrainingLabLandingScreen.prefab and replaced it with a dedicated CoachWidget prefab and script. Updated related UI prefabs and scripts to support the new widget structure and improved layout handling. Also adjusted GreenZebra.mat color values and made minor property updates to TrainingPlan and other widgets.

Add start stage index to TrainingPlanWidget

Introduces a serialized _startStageIndex field to TrainingPlanWidget and sets the stage progress index to this value on enable. Updates related prefabs to support this new property and adjusts UI layout for improved alignment and display.

Add TrainingLab button assets and TrainingProgramPopup

Introduced new button sprites and their meta files for the TrainingLab UI, including dark, default, unlock, and unlockable button variants. Renamed yellowish button asset for consistency. Added TrainingProgramPopup prefab and script, and updated several UI prefabs to use the new button assets and improved event handling. Also moved and refactored TrainMenuPopUp script for better organization.

Add date display to session score widgets

Introduced a date field and display for SessionScoreWidget and PreviousSessionScore prefabs. Updated GiveFeedbackView and TrainMenuPopUp to handle and pass session date data. Adjusted animation durations from 0.5s to 0.3s for smoother UI transitions. LessonItemWidget now displays dates in local time.

Refactor feedback UI flow and prefab anchors

Refactored GiveFeedbackView to separate initial state setup and removed hardcoded test data from OnEnable, now setting feedback data only when required. Updated TrainMenuPopUp to open GiveFeedbackView with test data via a new OpenUiView method. Adjusted UI prefab anchors and positions for TrainingLab screens and popups to improve layout consistency.

Add SessionProgressWidget and update TrainingLab UI

Introduces the SessionProgressWidget prefab and its associated script for the TrainingLab UI. Updates MyTrainingLabLandingScreen.prefab to remove old assignment UI elements and refactor layout, including changes to images, text, and widget structure. Also updates GiveFeedbackView.cs to integrate the new widget.

Add PreviousSessionScore widget to GiveFeedbackView

Introduced the PreviousSessionScore prefab and integrated it into the GiveFeedbackView UI and logic. Updated layout and anchoring in GiveFeedbackView and MyTrainingLabLandingScreen to accommodate the new widget. Adjusted related scripts and references to support displaying the previous session's score in the feedback flow.

Refactor feedback and video UI logic, improve UX

Updated GiveFeedbackView to improve button handling, feedback flow, and warning display. Integrated a CustomContentSizeFitter for dynamic UI sizing. Refactored VideoWidget to clarify and expand public API, improve documentation, and enhance playlist and playback controls. Cleaned up prefab and script references to support new logic.

Add feedback UI and logic for TrainingLab

Introduced new UI assets and prefabs for the TrainingLab feedback system, including yellow chat icon and rounded button. Added FeedbackRequestWidget and updated GiveFeedbackView to support dynamic feedback questions and answers, with logic for handling answer selection, warnings, and feedback sent state.

Moved several GameMode-related prefabs from Screens to Widgets for better organization. Updated UI elements to use a new sprite and adjusted color and pixel settings for consistency. Added VideoButtonWidget script and integrated it into the VideoNavButton prefab. Made layout and anchoring adjustments in TrainingLab and SessionProgressWidget prefabs.

analyses.message:
Add new TrainingLab widgets and update UI screens

Introduced new widgets for TrainingLab including MyTechniqueSessions, ProgramSelectorWidget, SmallReviewSummaryWidget, SmallSessionProgressWidget, and StandardButtonWidget. Updated CoachFeedbackView, GiveFeedbackView, MyTrainingLabLandingScreen prefabs and related scripts to integrate these widgets and improve UI layout and feedback presentation.

commit_details.message:
Add detailed XML documentation to UI scripts

Comprehensive XML doc comments were added to multiple UI-related scripts, including controllers, popups, and views. These comments describe class responsibilities, method behaviors, parameters, return values, and remarks for improved code maintainability and developer understanding. No functional changes were made.

Add sound button and label to VideoWidget

Introduced a sound toggle button and label text to the VideoWidget UI, including supporting prefab and controller changes. Added a new mute sound icon and updated GameReplayView to use it. VideoWidgetController now supports setting a caption and references the new UI elements.

Refactor GameMode UI prefabs and add VideoButtonWidget

Moved several GameMode-related prefabs from Screens to Widgets for better organization. Updated UI elements to use a new sprite and adjusted color and pixel settings for consistency. Added VideoButtonWidget script and integrated it into the VideoNavButton prefab. Made layout and anchoring adjustments in TrainingLab and SessionProgressWidget prefabs.

Add new TrainingLab widgets and update UI screens

Introduced new widgets for TrainingLab including MyTechniqueSessions, ProgramSelectorWidget, SmallReviewSummaryWidget, SmallSessionProgressWidget, and StandardButtonWidget. Updated CoachFeedbackView, GiveFeedbackView, MyTrainingLabLandingScreen prefabs and related scripts to integrate these widgets and improve UI layout and feedback presentation.
